ing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ba1b8bd3-02c0-44cb-a271-5028deabbdb2","uuid":"c770726d-f881-45cc-a538-7c34f3b91058","timestamp":"2026-03-22T16:51:15.559Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/.prizm-docs/root.prizm","content":"PRIZM_VERSION: 1.0\nPROJECT: PrizmClaw\nLANG: JavaScript (ESM), Node.js 22\nDESCRIPTION: Telegram Ôćĺ AI CLI bridge with web admin panel; bidirectional sync, pipeline orchestration\nENTRY: src/index.js\nTEST_CMD: node --test tests/**/*.test.js\n\nMODULE_INDEX:\n- src -> .prizm-docs/src/\n- src/adapters -> .prizm-docs/src/adapters.prizm\n- src/bot -> .prizm-docs/src/bot.prizm\n- src/http -> .prizm-docs/src/http.prizm\n- src/pipeline-infra -> .prizm-docs/src/pipeline-infra.prizm\n- src/routes -> .prizm-docs/src/routes.prizm\n- src/security -> .prizm-docs/src/security.prizm\n- src/services -> .prizm-docs/src/services.prizm\n- src/utils -> .prizm-docs/src/utils.prizm\n- public -> (static web panel assets ÔÇö no L1 doc)\n\nRULES:\n- All chat messages route through messageRouter.processMessage() ÔÇö never call executeAiCli directly for chat\n- Session keys: bound sessions use telegram:{chatId}, unbound web sessions use web:{sessionId}\n- Safe-to-modify config keys: LOG_LEVEL, REQUEST_TIMEOUT_MS, AI_CLI_HEARTBEAT_MS, MAX_PROMPT_CHARS, MAX_HISTORY_TURNS, SYSTEM_MONITOR_INTERVAL_MS, SESSION_TIMEOUT_MS, TASK_DEBOUNCE_MS\n- ANSI stripping happens in onAssistantChunk hook via ansiProcessChunk() ÔÇö never strip in final reply path\n- .btn:disabled uses pointer-events: none to prevent hover CSS from firing on disabled buttons\n\nUPDATED: 2026-03-23\n","numLines":28,"startLine":1,"totalLines":28}}}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_0198vJCeQ4Nv4wK7ZgS14yaJ","type":"tool_result","content":"     1Ôćĺ## PrizmKit Documentation Framework\n     2Ôćĺ\n     3ÔćĺThis project uses PrizmKit with the Prizm documentation system for AI-optimized progressive context loading.\n     4Ôćĺ\n     5Ôćĺ### Progressive Loading Protocol\n     6Ôćĺ- ON SESSION START: Always read `.prizm-docs/root.prizm` first (L0 ÔÇö project map)\n     7Ôćĺ- ON TASK: Read L1 (`.prizm-docs/<module>.prizm`) for relevant modules referenced in MODULE_INDEX\n     8Ôćĺ- ON FILE EDIT: Read L2 (`.prizm-docs/<module>/<submodule>.prizm`) before modifying files. Pay attention to TRAPS.\n     9Ôćĺ- NEVER load all .prizm docs at once. Load only what is needed for the current task.\n    10Ôćĺ\n    11Ôćĺ### Auto-Update Protocol\n    12Ôćĺ- BEFORE EVERY COMMIT: Update affected `.prizm-docs/` files\n    13Ôćĺ- Platform hooks (rules or UserPromptSubmit) will remind you automatically\n    14Ôćĺ- Use `/prizmkit-committer` for the complete commit workflow\n    15Ôćĺ\n    16Ôćĺ### Doc Format Rules\n    17Ôćĺ- All `.prizm` files use KEY: value format, not prose\n    18Ôćĺ- Size limits: L0 = 4KB, L1 = 3KB, L2 = 5KB\n    19Ôćĺ- Arrow notation (->) indicates load pointers to other .prizm docs\n    20Ôćĺ- DECISIONS and CHANGELOG are append-only (never delete entries)\n    21Ôćĺ\n    22Ôćĺ### Creating New L2 Docs\n    23Ôćĺ- When you first modify files in a sub-module that has no L2 doc:\n    24Ôćĺ  1. Read the source files in that sub-module\n    25Ôćĺ  2. Generate a new L2 `.prizm` file following Prizm specification\n    26Ôćĺ  3. Add a pointer in the parent L1 doc's SUBDIRS section\n    27Ôćĺ\n    28Ôćĺ### Available Commands\n    29ÔćĺRun `/prizm-kit` to see all available PrizmKit commands.\n    30Ôćĺ\n    31Ôćĺ### Fast Path for Simple Changes\n    32ÔćĺNot every change needs the full spec -> plan workflow. Use fast path for:\n    33Ôćĺ- Bug fixes with clear root cause, config tweaks, typo fixes, simple refactors\n    34Ôćĺ- Documentation-only changes, test additions for existing code\n    35Ôćĺ- Fast path: `/prizmkit-plan` (simplified) Ôćĺ `/prizmkit-implement` Ôćĺ `/prizmkit-committer`\n    36Ôćĺ\n    37ÔćĺUse the full workflow (/prizmkit-specify -> /prizmkit-plan -> /prizmkit-analyze -> /prizmkit-implement) for:\n    38Ôćĺ- New features, multi-file coordinated changes, architectural decisions, data model or API changes\n    39Ôćĺ\n    40Ôćĺ### F-018: Web-Telegram Bidirectional Sync\n    41Ôćĺ- DECISION: All chat messages (Web + Telegram) must route through `messageRouter.processMessage()` ÔÇö do not call `executeAiCli` directly for chat. This ensures shared session state and realtimeHub event publishing.\n    42Ôćĺ- DECISION: Session key strategy ÔÇö bound sessions use `telegram:{chatId}`, unbound Web sessions use `web:{sessionId}`. When a web session binds to a Telegram chat, both channels share the same session key.\n    43Ôćĺ- DECISION: `createSessionBindService()` uses deferred init pattern ÔÇö call `ensureReady()` before any sync method in async contexts. Persistence is fire-and-forget; use `flush()` in tests.\n    44Ôćĺ- INTERFACE: `createHttpServer({logger, sessionBindingsPath?})` ÔÇö optional `sessionBindingsPath` for test isolation\n    45Ôćĺ- KNOWN GAP: Runtime-created bindings via POST /api/bind do not auto-subscribe realtimeHub for cross-channel push. Only startup-loaded bindings get subscribed. Wire `bot._f018.subscribeCrossChannel(chatId)` from bind handler to fix.\n    46Ôćĺ\n    47Ôćĺ### F-020: Enhanced Terminal Output Streaming\n    48Ôćĺ- DECISION: ANSI stripping happens in `onAssistantChunk` hook via `ansiProcessChunk()` ÔÇö raw ANSI bytes from AI CLI stdout are never forwarded to Telegram. Do not strip in the final `replyText` path (already clean from streaming).\n    49Ôćĺ- DECISION: Smart segmentation (`segmentOutput`) replaces `splitMessage` ONLY in the streaming render path ÔÇö the cross-channel push path (`subscribeCrossChannel`) intentionally still uses `splitMessage` (out of scope, different code path).\n    50Ôćĺ- DECISION: Output history stores raw `routerResult.reply` (pre-split, pre-file-marker extraction) under key `telegram:{chatId}` ÔÇö ensures full output is preserved for /output retrieval.\n    51Ôćĺ- DECISION: `outputHistoryService` singleton lives in `output.js` and is re-exported to `telegram.js` ÔÇö tests inject mock via `handlerCtx.outputHistoryService` to avoid mutating shared state across test runs.\n    52Ôćĺ- INTERFACE: `processChunk(text)` from `src/utils/ansi-adapter.js` ÔÇö wraps each raw stdout chunk: strips ANSI then collapses `\\r` progress lines. Import as named `ansiProcessChunk` alias.\n    53Ôćĺ- INTERFACE: `segmentOutput(text, maxChunkSize=3800)` from `src/utils/output-segmenter.js` ÔÇö replaces `splitMessage` inside `render()` closure of `createEditableStreamPublisher`.\n    54Ôćĺ\n    55Ôćĺ### F-023: Web Button Hover Animation\n    56Ôćĺ- DECISION: `.btn:disabled` uses `pointer-events: none` in addition to `opacity: 0.6` ÔÇö ensures hover CSS rules never fire on disabled buttons, providing clean visual separation between enabled and disabled states.\n    57Ôćĺ- DECISION: Hover effect uses `transform: translateY(-1px)` + `filter: brightness(1.08)` on `.btn:hover` with `transition: transform 0.15s ease, filter 0.15s ease` on `.btn` ÔÇö applies to all button variants (primary, warning, ghost) without variant-specific overrides.\n    58Ôćĺ\n    59Ôćĺ### F-017: Runtime Config Manager\n    60Ôćĺ- DECISION: Safe-to-modify keys whitelist: LOG_LEVEL, REQUEST_TIMEOUT_MS, AI_CLI_HEARTBEAT_MS, MAX_PROMPT_CHARS, MAX_HISTORY_TURNS, SYSTEM_MONITOR_INTERVAL_MS, SESSION_TIMEOUT_MS, TASK_DEBOUNCE_MS ÔÇö all others are read-only via /config\n    61Ôćĺ- DECISION: Hot-reload via `process.env[key] = newValue` ÔÇö modifying process.env directly makes changes immediately visible to all modules that re-read config at call time (not frozen objects)\n    62Ôćĺ- DECISION: `configService.originalEnvValues` uses lazy capture ÔÇö if env var not present at module init, setConfig captures it on first modification. Reset relies on this map; always call setConfig before reset in tests that set env after module import.\n    63Ôćĺ- INTERFACE: `configService.{getAllConfig, getConfig, setConfig, resetConfig, isSafeConfigKey}` ÔÇö all async, exported from `src/services/config-service.js`\n    64Ôćĺ\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ba1b8bd3-02c0-44cb-a271-5028deabbdb2","uuid":"8bc56e91-6663-4dcb-a53b-f43225f98ddf","timestamp":"2026-03-22T16:51:15.560Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/CLAUDE.md","content":"## PrizmKit Documentation Framework\n\nThis project uses PrizmKit with the Prizm documentation system for AI-optimized progressive context loading.\n\n### Progressive Loading Protocol\n- ON SESSION START: Always read `.prizm-docs/root.prizm` first (L0 ÔÇö project map)\n- ON TASK: Read L1 (`.prizm-docs/<module>.prizm`) for relevant modules referenced in MODULE_INDEX\n- ON FILE EDIT: Read L2 (`.prizm-docs/<module>/<submodule>.prizm`) before modifying files. Pay attention to TRAPS.\n- NEVER load all .prizm docs at once. Load only what is needed for the current task.\n\n### Auto-Update Protocol\n- BEFORE EVERY COMMIT: Update affected `.prizm-docs/` files\n- Platform hooks (rules or UserPromptSubmit) will remind you automatically\n- Use `/prizmkit-committer` for the complete commit workflow\n\n### Doc Format Rules\n- All `.prizm` files use KEY: value format, not prose\n- Size limits: L0 = 4KB, L1 = 3KB, L2 = 5KB\n- Arrow notation (->) indicates load pointers to other .prizm docs\n- DECISIONS and CHANGELOG are append-only (never delete entries)\n\n### Creating New L2 Docs\n- When you first modify files in a sub-module that has no L2 doc:\n  1. Read the source files in that sub-module\n  2. Generate a new L2 `.prizm` file following Prizm specification\n  3. Add a pointer in the parent L1 doc's SUBDIRS section\n\n### Available Commands\nRun `/prizm-kit` to see all available PrizmKit commands.\n\n### Fast Path for Simple Changes\nNot every change needs the full spec -> plan workflow. Use fast path for:\n- Bug fixes with clear root cause, config tweaks, typo fixes, simple refactors\n- Documentation-only changes, test additions for existing code\n- Fast path: `/prizmkit-plan` (simplified) Ôćĺ `/prizmkit-implement` Ôćĺ `/prizmkit-committer`\n\nUse the full workflow (/prizmkit-specify -> /prizmkit-plan -> /prizmkit-analyze -> /prizmkit-implement) for:\n- New features, multi-file coordinated changes, architectural decisions, data model or API changes\n\n### F-018: Web-Telegram Bidirectional Sync\n- DECISION: All chat messages (Web + Telegram) must route through `messageRouter.processMessage()` ÔÇö do not call `executeAiCli` directly for chat. This ensures shared session state and realtimeHub event publishing.\n- DECISION: Session key strategy ÔÇö bound sessions use `telegram:{chatId}`, unbound Web sessions use `web:{sessionId}`. When a web session binds to a Telegram chat, both channels share the same session key.\n- DECISION: `createSessionBindService()` uses deferred init pattern ÔÇö call `ensureReady()` before any sync method in async contexts. Persistence is fire-and-forget; use `flush()` in tests.\n- INTERFACE: `createHttpServer({logger, sessionBindingsPath?})` ÔÇö optional `sessionBindingsPath` for test isolation\n- KNOWN GAP: Runtime-created bindings via POST /api/bind do not auto-subscribe realtimeHub for cross-channel push. Only startup-loaded bindings get subscribed. Wire `bot._f018.subscribeCrossChannel(chatId)` from bind handler to fix.\n\n### F-020: Enhanced Terminal Output Streaming\n- DECISION: ANSI stripping happens in `onAssistantChunk` hook via `ansiProcessChunk()` ÔÇö raw ANSI bytes from AI CLI stdout are never forwarded to Telegram. Do not strip in the final `replyText` path (already clean from streaming).\n- DECISION: Smart segmentation (`segmentOutput`) replaces `splitMessage` ONLY in the streaming render path ÔÇö the cross-channel push path (`subscribeCrossChannel`) intentionally still uses `splitMessage` (out of scope, different code path).\n- DECISION: Output history stores raw `routerResult.reply` (pre-split, pre-file-marker extraction) under key `telegram:{chatId}` ÔÇö ensures full output is preserved for /output retrieval.\n- DECISION: `outputHistoryService` singleton lives in `output.js` and is re-exported to `telegram.js` ÔÇö tests inject mock via `handlerCtx.outputHistoryService` to avoid mutating shared state across test runs.\n- INTERFACE: `processChunk(text)` from `src/utils/ansi-adapter.js` ÔÇö wraps each raw stdout chunk: strips ANSI then collapses `\\r` progress lines. Import as named `ansiProcessChunk` alias.\n- INTERFACE: `segmentOutput(text, maxChunkSize=3800)` from `src/utils/output-segmenter.js` ÔÇö replaces `splitMessage` inside `render()` closure of `createEditableStreamPublisher`.\n\n### F-023: Web Button Hover Animation\n- DECISION: `.btn:disabled` uses `pointer-events: none` in addition to `opacity: 0.6` ÔÇö ensures hover CSS rules never fire on disabled buttons, providing clean visual separation between enabled and disabled states.\n- DECISION: Hover effect uses `transform: translateY(-1px)` + `filter: brightness(1.08)` on `.btn:hover` with `transition: transform 0.15s ease, filter 0.15s ease` on `.btn` ÔÇö applies to all button variants (primary, warning, ghost) without variant-specific overrides.\n\n### F-017: Runtime Config Manager\n- DECISION: Safe-to-modify keys whitelist: LOG_LEVEL, REQUEST_TIMEOUT_MS, AI_CLI_HEARTBEAT_MS, MAX_PROMPT_CHARS, MAX_HISTORY_TURNS, SYSTEM_MONITOR_INTERVAL_MS, SESSION_TIMEOUT_MS, TASK_DEBOUNCE_MS ÔÇö all others are read-only via /config\n- DECISION: Hot-reload via `process.env[key] = newValue` ÔÇö modifying process.env directly makes changes immediately visible to all modules that re-read config at call time (not frozen objects)\n- DECISION: `configService.originalEnvValues` uses lazy capture ÔÇö if env var not present at module init, setConfig captures it on first modification. Reset relies on this map; always call setConfig before reset in tests that set env after module import.\n- INTERFACE: `configService.{getAllConfig, getConfig, setConfig, resetConfig, isSafeConfigKey}` ÔÇö all async, exported from `src/services/config-service.js`\n","numLines":64,"startLine":1,"totalLines":64}}}
